<br>
A rogue mob *should* manuever to backstab.  However, if they could get the mobs to behave more like players to be more challenging, then also the difficulty of the mobs needs to be decreased.  IE A rogue mob shouldn't have the hitpoints of a warrior mob, it should have very low hitpoints, but be hard to hit.  And you should be able to root it and pin it somewhere, as well, that would really add a whole extra dimension.  A wizard mobs melee should be &quot;miss..miss...miss.&quot;...   <p>56 Magician-Unguilded-Firiona Vie-More active culture than a carton of Yoplait</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=mithlin>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/16/02 9:36:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2337.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If mobs moved</span><hr size=1> What, you don't think wizard mobs should be beating you to a pulp and then casting spells on you to add insult to injury? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ak'Anon Sex Symbol</span><br>  Posts: 624<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/16/02 9:58:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2337.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If mobs moved</span><hr size=1> There is absolutely NOTHING wrong with mobs behaving more realistically and reacting with more sophisticated AI tactics.... and thus being potentially more challenging to players.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The caveat is.... if Verant did this, they they have ZERO reason to handicap mobs with built-in cheats (e.g. mob casters with near infinite mana) </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Ideally, if I were the Ideal Gaming Company, I would program my mobs with incredibly brilliant AI that made them behave in ways that players typically react.... cunning, clever, deceitful, tricky, resourceful, tactical. And once I can accomplish this, there would be ZERO reason why the AI monsters I created should resort to built-in cheats such as being able to cast spells with infinite mana pool, or being able to cast spells while running (which is normally an impossibility for EQ player characters).  <br>
<br>
Obviously.... Verant and other MMORPG companies have a long ways to go until they can provide reasonably clever AIs... therefore, they STILL resort to cheats as the primary way of the AI providing challenge for human players such as you and me. <br>
<br>
